                            <comment id="223032" author="adilger" created="Sat, 10 Mar 2018 08:25:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Recent test runs are in the 3s range.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="43832" author="adilger" created="Mon, 27 Aug 2012 17:56:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shadow, the test you added in commit c9590221dc43dd5e7a7ede389f0a7d9cf566e5bf takes a very long time to run, 939s in one recent case.  Could you please look at this test and find a way to speed it up, without removing the functionality?  I think reducing AT_max on the OSS for just this test should be enough, but since you wrote the test I want to make sure that this will not avoid the problem that it was trying to trigger.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
